  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Microsoft&#174; Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) 3.5 <li>Microsoft Visual Studio&#174; 2008</li></li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>What to Do</h1>\n  <p>If your Partner Applications needs to be Authenticated when calling WCF services, consider using Client Certificate Authentication. </p>\n  <h1>When</h1>\n  <p>Consider using this guideline when using Certificate Authentication in business-to-business (B2B) scenarios.</p>\n  <h1>How</h1>\n  <p>If you have partners that need to consume your services, consider using transport security with client certificate authentication. Client certificate authentication allows clients to authenticate without prompting for a username and password. </p>\n  <p>In order to support client certificate authentication, you will need to add a &lt;clientCertificate&gt; reference to the client config file. The following client config example links the client certificate to the binding:</p>\n  <pre>    &lt;behaviors&gt;<br />      &lt;endpointBehaviors&gt;<br />        &lt;behavior name=\"ClientCertificateBehavior\"&gt;<br />          &lt;clientCredentials&gt;<br />            &lt;clientCertificate findValue=\"client.com\" storeLocation=\"CurrentUser\" storeName=\"My\" x509FindType=\"FindBySubjectName\" /&gt;<br />          &lt;/clientCredentials&gt;<br />        &lt;/behavior&gt;<br />      &lt;/endpointBehaviors&gt;<br />    &lt;/behaviors&gt;</pre>\n  <hr />\n  <p>Adapted from Microsoft patterns & practices guidance.</p>"
